# Cursor Rules — Big Idea Games Webapp Starter

## Tech Stack
- React 19 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- Vite for bundling
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config)
- shadcn/ui for UI components
- Lucide React for icons

## Code Standards

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript strictly — no `any`, no `as` casts unless truly necessary
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Use `const` assertions where applicable
- Export types alongside components when they're part of the public API

### Components
- One component per file, PascalCase naming (e.g., `PlayerCard.tsx`)
- Keep components small and composable (< 150 lines ideal)
- Use shadcn/ui components — don't reinvent buttons, cards, inputs, etc.
- Import from `@/components/ui/` for shadcn components
- Put app-specific components in `@/components/`

### Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively — no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Follow the design token system — **never hardcode colors, spacing, or sizes**
- Use CSS custom properties from `src/styles/globals.css` for theming
- Reference semantic colors: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-surface`, `border-border`, etc.
- For accent colors, use `var(--accent-primary)`, `var(--accent-secondary)`, etc.
- Responsive: mobile-first approach using Tailwind breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- Dark mode is default; light mode uses `.light` class on root

### Design Token Colors (defined in globals.css)
```
--accent-primary    → lime (wins, primary stats)
--accent-secondary  → cyan (high priority)
--accent-tertiary   → blue (lower priority)
--accent-alert      → yellow (live states, alerts)
--accent-danger     → red (errors, losses)
```

### Patterns
- No magic strings — use constants or enums
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Prefer named exports for components
- Keep state minimal and close to where it's used
- Use `import type` for type-only imports

### File Organization
```
src/
├── components/     → App-specific components
│   └── ui/         → shadcn/ui (don't edit manually)
├── lib/            → Utilities, helpers, constants
├── styles/         → Global CSS, design tokens
├── App.tsx         → Main app component
└── main.tsx        → Entry point
```

### Don'ts
- Don't use inline styles (use Tailwind)
- Don't create new CSS files (use Tailwind utilities)
- Don't hardcode hex colors (use design tokens)
- Don't install new UI component libraries (use shadcn/ui)
- Don't use `React.FC` — use plain function declarations
- Don't use default exports for non-page components
